---
import "../styles/global.css"
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content="The workspace where humans and AI collaborate as colleagues." />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#111111" />
    <meta name="color-scheme" content="dark" />
    <title>Synatra</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen bg-surface-bg antialiased">

    <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">

      <header class="pt-16 pb-32 md:pt-24 md:pb-40">
        <a href="/" class="inline-block text-text-secondary text-base font-medium tracking-tight hover:text-text-primary transition-colors">
          Synatra
        </a>
      </header>

      <section class="pb-40 md:pb-56">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-medium leading-[1.2] tracking-tight text-text-primary">
          The best tools<br />disappear entirely.
        </h1>
      </section>

      <section class="pb-32 md:pb-40">
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
          We stopped building dashboards.<br />
          We stopped designing forms.<br />
          We just say what we need.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="pb-40 md:pb-56 border-t border-surface-border-muted pt-16">
        <div class="space-y-16">
          <article>
            <h2 class="text-text-primary text-lg font-medium mb-3">Software should feel like a colleague.</h2>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Not a tool you operate. Not a dashboard you check. A presence that works beside you, thinks with you, and speaks when it matters.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h2 class="text-text-primary text-lg font-medium mb-3">Building is the old way.</h2>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Every form you build is debt. Every dashboard is maintenance. The interface should emerge from the conversation, exist for a moment, then dissolve.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h2 class="text-text-primary text-lg font-medium mb-3">Quiet until it counts.</h2>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">It won't interrupt you with noise. But when something matters, it finds you. That's the difference between assistant and colleague.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h2 class="text-text-primary text-lg font-medium mb-3">Built for developers, by developers.</h2>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">No unnecessary abstraction. No black boxes. Simple when you use it, transparent when you look inside. Every line of code is open source.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="py-32 md:py-48 border-t border-surface-border-muted">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-border-muted">
          <video
            class="w-full"
            controls
            playsinline
            preload="metadata"
          >
            <source src="/videos/demo.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="py-32 md:py-48 border-t border-surface-border-muted">
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed mb-10">
          This is not another tool.<br />
          This is how work becomes.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://synatrahq.com/login"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-text-primary text-sm hover:text-text-secondary transition-colors group"
        >
          <span>Begin</span>
          <span class="transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </section>

      <footer class="pb-16 pt-16 border-t border-surface-border-muted flex items-center justify-between text-xs text-text-disabled">
        <a href="https://github.com/synatrahq/synatra" class="hover:text-text-muted transition-colors">
          Open source
        </a>
        <span>For those who believe</span>
      </footer>

    </main>

  </body>
</html>
